  "text": "News Opening day energy! Photo: Apple Apple’s retail footprint in South Florida expanded Friday with the opening of its newest location, Apple Miami Worldcenter. A big opening-day crowd — including Apple execs Deirdre O’Brien and Eddy Cue — swamped the sleek new store, Apple’s 10th retail location in Miami. “Miami is a city with a history, culture and life all its own, and we are thrilled to capture that energy with Apple Miami Worldcenter in downtown Miami,” said Deirdre O’Brien, Apple’s senior vice president of retail and people, in a press release. Apple Miami Worldcenter showcases the company’s commitment to sustainability, accessibility and community engagement in the heart of downtown. And it’s the city’s first store with a dedicated Apple Pickup area. Apple Miami Worldcenter store opens Friday, January 24 The new Apple Miami Worldcenter store in downtown Miami includes local materials in its construction.Photo: Apple The large new Apple Store follows other glitzy Miami openings like this and this. Apple Miami Worldcenter features an innovative design that incorporates regionally sourced mass timber and low-carbon materials. That significantly reduced its construction’s environmental impact, Apple said. L Like all Apple facilities, the store operates on 100% renewable energy and maintains carbon-neutral operations. The location’s biophilic design elements include grounds and a roof adorned with plants and flora that pay homage to Miami’s rich Latin American heritage. The store aims to create an inclusive environment where customers can explore the latest Apple products, like iPhone 16 and Vision Pro, while receiving personalized support and participating in educational programs, Apple noted. Prominent accessibility features Apple team members help customers explore Apple Intelligence features across Apple’s latest iPhone, iPad and Mac lineups.Photo: Apple The store’s design makes accessibility features prominent, with varied table and seating heights accommodating diverse needs. The location offers enhanced navigation space for wheelchair users and includes portable hearing loops for customers with hearing aids. The accessibility features extend to the store’s Today at Apple sessions, where an assistive listening loop ensures all participants can fully engage in the programming. First dedicated Apple Pickup area in Miami Apple Miami Worldcenter is the first Apple Store in the city to feature a dedicated Apple Pickup area, making purchases easier.Photo: Apple In a first for Miami, the store introduces a dedicated Apple Pickup area. It streamlines the process for customers who prefer to shop online and collect their purchases in-store. More than 15o team member staff the new location, ready to assist customers with product demonstrations, financing options and trade-in programs. Apple Miami Worldcenter features a biophilic design, connecting customers to the beautiful green spaces surrounding the store — and on the roof.Photo: Apple To commemorate its opening, Apple Miami Worldcenter will host special Today at Apple sessions highlighting the store’s environmental design features. The store will also partner with Influur for Made for Business community events. That will offer local entrepreneurs hands-on experience with Apple’s business tools across iPhone, iPad and Mac platforms. Apple Miami Worldcenter store: Downtown Miami’s source for Apple gear Customers can experience Vision Pro at the demo area in Apple Miami Worldcenter.Photo: Apple The store opening reinforces Apple’s growing presence in South Florida, where the company employs nearly 2,000 team members. Beyond retail operations, Apple maintains strong community ties through educational initiatives, including a partnership with Miami Dade College. It aims to create opportunities for learners of all ages. Visitors to Apple Miami Worldcenter can explore the company’s latest products, including iPhone 16, new Mac models powered by the M4 chip, Apple Watch Series 10 and various AirPods options. The store’s Group Booking feature allows families, friends and colleagues to schedule Today at Apple sessions together. Opening-day pictures from Apple Miami Worldcenter Customers show off commemorative Apple Miami Worldcenter picnic blankets.Photo: Apple You’re never too young for Apple gear!Photo: Apple A big crowd showed up for the store’s opening.Photo: Apple Apple execs Deirdre O’Brien and Eddy Cue greet customers in front of Apple Miami Worldcenter.Photo: Apple Opening-day shoppers check out Apple Watches at Apple Miami Worldcenter.Photo: Apple A customer explores the latest Mac lineup at Apple Miami Worldcenter on opening day.Photo: Apple Apple Miami Worldcenter was packed on opening day.Photo: Apple An Apple team member assists a customer at the new Miami store’s iPad display.Photo: Apple Source: Apple We originally published this post on Apple Miami Worldcenter on January 22, 2025. We updated it after the store’s grand opening.",
