her glitzy Miami openings \u003ca href=\"https://www.cultofmac.com/news/apples-stunning-new-miami-store-pays-homage-to-areas-nautical-history\" data-lasso-id=\"1641681278\"\u003elike this\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\"https://www.cultofmac.com/news/unique-features-make-miami-apple-store-look-like-no-other\" data-lasso-id=\"1641681279\"\u003ethis\u003c/a\u003e. Apple Miami Worldcenter features an innovative design that incorporates regionally sourced mass timber and low-carbon materials. That significantly reduced its construction’s environmental impact, Apple said. L\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLike all Apple facilities, the store operates on 100% renewable energy and maintains carbon-neutral operations. The location’s biophilic design elements include grounds and a roof adorned with plants and flora that pay homage to Miami’s rich Latin American heritage.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe store aims to create an inclusive environment where customers can explore the latest Apple products, like \u003ca href=\"https://www.cultofmac.com/iphone\" data-lasso-id=\"1641681280\"\u003eiPhone\u003c/a\u003e 16 and \u003ca href=\"https://www.cultofmac.com/vision-pro\" data-lasso-id=\"1641681281\"\u003eVision Pro\u003c/a\u003e, while receiving personalized support and participating in educational programs, Apple noted.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3\u003eProminent accessibility features\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cfigure id=\"29\" aria-labelledby=\"figcaption_29\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.cultofmac.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Apple-Miami-Worldcenter-media-preview-store-interior_big.jpg.large_2x.jpg\" data-lasso-id=\"1641681282\"\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" title=\"Apple Miami Worldcenter media preview store interior_big.jpg.large_2x\" src=\"https://www.cultofmac.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Apple-Miami-Worldcenter-media-preview-store-interior_big.jpg.large_2x.jpg\" alt=\"Apple Miami Worldcenter store\" width=\"1960\" height=\"1308\" srcset=\"https://www.cultofmac.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Apple-Miami-Worldcenter-media-preview-store-interior_big.jpg.large_2x.jpg 1960w, https://www.cultofmac.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Apple-Miami-Worldcenter-media-preview-store-interior_big.jpg.large_2x-400x267.jpg 400w, https://www.cultofmac.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Apple-Miami-Worldcenter-media-preview-store-interior_big.jpg.large_2x-1440x961.jpg.webp 1440w, https://www.cultofmac.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Apple-Miami-Worldcenter-media-preview-store-interior_big.jpg.large_2x-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://www.cultofmac.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Apple-Miami-Worldcenter-media-preview-store-interior_big.jpg.large_2x-350x234.jpg 350w, https://www.cultofmac.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Apple-Miami-Worldcenter-media-preview-store-interior_big.jpg.large_2x-400x267@2x.jpg 800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1960px) 100vw, 1960px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cfigcaption id=\"figcaption_29\"\u003eApple team members help customers explore Apple Intelligence features across Apple’s latest iPhone, iPad and Mac lineups.\u003cbr/\u003e\u003cspan\u003ePhoto: Apple\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe store’s design makes accessibility features prominent, with varied table and seating heights accommodating diverse needs. The location offers enhanced navigation space for wheelchair users and includes portable hearing loops for customers with hearing aids.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe accessibility features extend to the store’s Today at Apple sessions, where an assistive listening loop ensures all participants can fully engage in the programming.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3\u003eFirst dedicated Apple Pickup area in Miami\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cfigure id=\"29\" aria-labelledby=\"figcaption_29\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.cultofmac.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Apple-Miami-Worldcenter-media-preview-Genius-Bar-and-Apple-Pickup_big.jpg.large_2x.jpg\" data-lasso-id=\"1641681288\"\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" title=\"Apple Miami Worldcenter media preview Genius Bar and Apple Pickup_big.jpg.large_2x\" src=\"https://www.cultofmac.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Apple-Miami-Worldcenter-media-preview-Genius-Bar-and-Apple-Pickup_big.jpg.large_2x.jpg\" alt=\"Apple Miami Worldcenter store\" width=\"1960\" height=\"1312\" srcset=\"https://www.cultofmac.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Apple-Miami-Worldcenter-media-preview-Genius-Bar-and-Apple-Pickup_big.jpg.large_2x.jpg 1960w, https://www.cultofmac.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Apple-Miami-Worldcenter-media-preview-Genius-Bar-and-Apple-Pickup_big.jpg.large_2x-400x268.jpg 400w, https://www.cultofmac.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Apple-Miami-Worldcenter-media-preview-Genius-Bar-and-Apple-Pickup_big.jpg.large_2x-1440x964.jpg.webp 1440w, https://www.cultofmac.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Apple-Miami-Worldcenter-media-preview-Genius-Bar-and-Apple-Pickup_big.jpg.large_2x-1536x1028.jpg 1536w, https://www.cultofmac.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Apple-Miami-Worldcenter-media-preview-Genius-Bar-and-Apple-Pickup_big.jpg.large_2x-350x234.jpg 350w, https://www.cultofmac.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Apple-Miami-Worldcenter-media-preview-Genius-Bar-and-Apple-Pickup_big.jpg.large_2x-400x268@2x.jpg 800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1960px) 100vw, 1960px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cfigcaption id=\"figcaption_29\"\u003eApple Miami Worldcenter is the first Apple Store in the city to feature a dedicated Apple Pickup area, making purchases easier.\u003cbr/\u003e\u003cspan\u003ePhoto: Apple\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn a first for Miami, the store introduces a dedicated Apple Pickup area. It streamlines the process for customers who prefer to shop online and collect their purchases in-store. More than 15o team member staff the new location, ready to assist customers with product demonstrations, financing options and trade-in programs.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure id=\"29\" aria-labelledby=\"figcaption_29\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.cultofmac.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Apple-Miami-Worldcenter-GIF.gif\" data-lasso-id=\"1641681290\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" title=\"Apple Miami Worldcenter GIF\" src=\"https://www.cultofmac.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Apple-Miami-Worldcenter-GIF.gif\" alt=\"Apple Miami Worldcenter store\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cfigcaption id=\"figcaption_29\"\u003eApple Miami Worldcenter features a biophilic design, connecting customers to the beautiful green spaces surrounding the store — and on the roof.\u003cbr/\u003e\u003cspan\u003ePhoto: Apple\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTo commemorate its opening, Apple Miami Worldcenter will host special Today at Apple sessions highlighting the store’s environmental design features. The store will also partner with Influur for Made for Business community events. That will offer local entrepreneurs hands-on experience with Apple’s business tools across iPhone, iPad and Mac platforms.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cspan data-ez-ph-id=\"912\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003ch3\u003eApple Miami Worldcenter store: Downtown Miami’s source for Apple gear\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cfigure id=\"29\" aria-labelledby=\"figcaption_29\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.cultofmac.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Apple-Miami-Worldcenter-media-preview-team-member-fitting-customer-with-Apple-Vision-Pro_big.jpg.large_2x.jpg\" data-lasso-id=\"1641681289\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" title=\"Apple Miami Worldcenter media preview team member fitting customer with Apple Vision Pro_big.jpg.large_2x\" src=\"https://www.cultofmac.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Apple-Miami-Worldcenter-media-preview-team-member-fitting-customer-with-Apple-Vision-Pro_big.jpg.large_2x.jpg\" alt=\"Apple Miami Worldcenter store\" width=\"1960\" height=\"1300\" srcset=\"https://www.cultofmac.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Apple-Miami-Worldcenter-media-preview-team-member-fitting-customer-with-Apple-Vision-Pro_big.jpg.large_2x.jpg 1960w, https://www.cultofmac.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Apple-Miami-Worldcenter-media-preview-team-member-fitting-customer-with-Apple-Vision-Pro_big.jpg.large_2x-400x265.jpg 400w, https://www.cultofmac.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Apple-Miami-Worldcenter-media-preview-team-member-fitting-customer-with-Apple-Vision-Pro_big.jpg.large_2x-1440x955.jpg.webp 1440w, https://www.cultofmac.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Apple-Miami-Worldcenter-media-preview-team-member-fitting-customer-with-Apple-Vision-Pro_big.jpg.large_2x-1536x1019.jpg 1536w, https://www.cultofmac.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Apple-Miami-Worldcenter-media-preview-team-member-fitting-customer-with-Apple-Vision-Pro_big.jpg.large_2x-350x232.jpg 350w, https://www.cultofmac.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Apple-Miami-Worldcenter-media-preview-team-member-fitting-customer-with-Apple-Vision-Pro_big.jpg.large_2x-400x265@2x.jpg 800w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1960px) 100vw, 1960px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cfigcaption id=\"figcaption_29\"\u003eCustomers can experience Vision Pro at the demo area in Apple Miami Worldcenter.\u003cbr/\u003e\u003cspan\u003ePhoto: Apple\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe store opening reinforces Apple’s growing presence in South Florida, where the company employs nearly 2,000 team members. Beyond retail operations, Apple maintains strong community ties through educational initiatives, including a partnership with Miami Dade College. It aims to create opportunities for learners of all ages.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eVisitors to Apple Miami Worldcenter can explore the company’s latest products, including iPhone 16, new Mac models powered by the M4 chip, Apple Watch Series 10 and various AirPods options. The store’s Group Booking feature allows families, friends and colleagues to schedule Today at Apple sessions together.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3\u003eOpening-da